<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4734876>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 13. The holotype mandibles of Citipati osmolskae IGM 100/978 (top) and Oviraptor philoceratops AMNH 6517 (bottom) in left lateral view (not to scale). The Oviraptor mandible has been digitally compressed to minimize the separation at two breaks in the dentary. Lines are drawn between topologically comparable points on the two mandibles to illustrate the proportionately greater length of the anterior part of the O. philoceratops mandible." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4734876/files/figure.png" .

